You are  given an array arr of size n. 
Your task is to write a recursive function that checks if the array is a "mirror image" of itself. 
An array is considered a mirror image if the first half is the reverse of the second half.

bool isMirrorImage(vector<int>& arr, int n){
        static int i=0;
        if(i>=n/2) return true;
        if(arr[i]!=arr[n-i-1]) return false;
        i++;
        return isMirrorImage(arr,n);
}
